it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface Semantic.SemanticAxiom<S,Y>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the semantic of all the element in the axiom set.
    Y - the type of Semantic.Axioms described by this container.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MORAxioms.DataSemantic, MORAxioms.ObjectSemantic
    Enclosing interface:
    Semantic

    public static interface Semantic.SemanticAxiom<S,Y>
    The container for Semantic.Axioms with a specific Semantic.

    It describes an Semantic.Axioms set that are all referring to a given semantic. It is mainly used to describes the values of data or object properties (i.e.: Semantic.Axioms), when the Semantic is such a property.

      • getSemantic

        S getSemantic()
        Represents the semantic (i.e.: data or object property) that aggregates all getValues() (i.e.: Semantic.Axioms).
        Returns:
        the semantic of the Semantic.Axioms described in this container.

      • getValues

        Semantic.Axioms<Y> getValues()
        Represents the Semantic.Axioms of this container. All those values are described by the same getSemantic().
        Returns:
        the axioms contained in this container.

      • getNewData

        Semantic.SemanticAxiom<S,Y> getNewData(java.util.Set<Y> values)
        It should create a new instance of this object that preserve the semantic but assign new values to it. It is used during synchronisation by Semantic.SemanticAxioms.SynchronisationMultiIntent.
        Parameters:
        values - the new data to be assigned to the same semantic.
        Returns:
        a new object with the same getSemantic() but new values.
